1
00:00:16,513 --> 00:00:22,110
We're just two little girls
From Little Rock

2
00:00:22,313 --> 00:00:27,626
We lived on the wrong side
Of the tracks

3
00:00:27,833 --> 00:00:30,188
But the gentlemen friends
Who used to call

4
00:00:30,433 --> 00:00:32,708
They never did seem to mind at all

5
00:00:32,953 --> 00:00:37,663
They came to the wrong side
Of the tracks

6
00:00:38,433 --> 00:00:43,461
Then someone broke my heart
In Little Rock

7
00:00:43,713 --> 00:00:48,741
So I up and left the pieces there

8
00:00:48,993 --> 00:00:51,666
Like a little lost lamb I roamed about

9
00:00:51,913 --> 00:00:54,268
I came to New York and I found out

10
00:00:54,513 --> 00:00:59,064
That men are the same way everywhere

11
00:00:59,633 --> 00:01:05,424
I was young and determined
To be wined and dined and ermined

12
00:01:05,633 --> 00:01:09,865
And I worked at it
All around the clock

13
00:01:10,833 --> 00:01:13,393
Now one of these days
In my fancy clothes

14
00:01:13,633 --> 00:01:18,912
I'm goin' back home and punch the nose
Of the one who broke my heart

15
00:01:19,153 --> 00:01:21,713
The one who broke my heart

16
00:01:21,953 --> 00:01:25,309
The one who broke my heart
In Little Rock

17
00:01:25,553 --> 00:01:29,626
Little Rock, Little Rock
Little Rock

18
00:02:55,753 --> 00:03:01,146
I learned an awful lot in Little Rock

19
00:03:01,353 --> 00:03:06,586
And here's some advice
I'd like to share

20
00:03:07,433 --> 00:03:09,788
Find a gentleman

21
00:03:09,993 --> 00:03:15,147
Who is shy or bold

22
00:03:15,513 --> 00:03:19,472
Or short or tall

23
00:03:19,713 --> 00:03:25,231
Or young or old

24
00:03:25,713 --> 00:03:30,264
As long as the guy's a millionaire

25
00:03:30,753 --> 00:03:35,986
For a kid from a small street
I did very well on Wall Street

26
00:03:36,233 --> 00:03:41,387
Though I never owned a share of stock

27
00:03:41,633 --> 00:03:43,908
And now that I'm known
In the biggest banks

28
00:03:44,153 --> 00:03:46,621
I'm a-goin' back home
And give my thanks

29
00:03:46,833 --> 00:03:49,472
To the one who broke my heart

30
00:03:49,673 --> 00:03:52,062
The one who broke my heart

31
00:03:52,273 --> 00:03:55,663
The one who broke my heart

32
00:03:59,353 --> 00:04:04,029
In Little Rock

33
00:04:18,153 --> 00:04:20,542
Dorothy, wait a minute.

34
00:04:23,793 --> 00:04:27,581
Louie, ask Mr. Esmond to come
to our dressing room.

35
00:04:27,793 --> 00:04:31,308
-Yes, Miss Blake.
-Why the rush? He won't run away.

36
00:04:31,553 --> 00:04:34,306
-l know, but l can't wait.
-For what?

37
00:04:34,553 --> 00:04:37,113
Didn't you notice?
His pocket was bulging.

38
00:04:37,353 --> 00:04:39,105
lt's a bag of gumdrops.

39
00:04:39,353 --> 00:04:44,347
lt was square, like a box for a ring.
l think he's got a present for me.

40
00:04:44,593 --> 00:04:48,142
Only you can be on-stage
with a spotlight in your eye...

41
00:04:48,353 --> 00:04:51,186
...and still see a diamond
in a man's pocket.

42
00:04:52,273 --> 00:04:54,264
Thank you, Louie.

43
00:05:03,113 --> 00:05:06,992
-Mr. Esmond. Pray, come in.
-Thank you, l'd love to.

44
00:05:07,193 --> 00:05:08,865
-Hi, Gus.
-Good evening.

45
00:05:09,113 --> 00:05:12,901
-You were wonderful. Magnificent!
-Thank you.

46
00:05:13,153 --> 00:05:17,704
-You were good too.
-Gee, that makes me all warm inside.

47
00:05:17,913 --> 00:05:21,303
-Mr. Esmond!
-ls it the right size?

48
00:05:21,513 --> 00:05:26,382
lt can never be too big.
Do you think it's too small, Dorothy?

49
00:05:27,753 --> 00:05:31,712
-lt should have a highball around it.
-Does it fit your finger?

50
00:05:31,953 --> 00:05:34,183
Yes, it fits perfect.

51
00:05:34,433 --> 00:05:39,063
Daddy, l'll bet you made me
the happiest girl in the world.

52
00:05:43,273 --> 00:05:46,504
What do you do,
put Novocaine on your lipstick?

53
00:05:46,753 --> 00:05:50,462
Daddy? Daddy?
May l tell Dorothy?

54
00:05:50,673 --> 00:05:52,265
lf you wish.

55
00:05:52,513 --> 00:05:55,710
Dorothy, Mr. Esmond and l
are getting married.

56
00:05:55,953 --> 00:05:59,423
-To each other?
-Of course. Who else to?

57
00:05:59,673 --> 00:06:04,144
l always figured Lorelei would end up
with the Secretary of the Treasury.

58
00:06:04,353 --> 00:06:08,141
-We're sailing on the Isle de Paris.
-''Ile'' de Paris.

59
00:06:08,353 --> 00:06:12,904
-We're getting married in Europe.
-Why not get married here, then go?

60
00:06:13,113 --> 00:06:15,707
-Or is that old-fashioned?
-We've made our plans.

61
00:06:15,873 --> 00:06:16,783
(KNOCKING)

62
00:06:16,953 --> 00:06:18,147
Come in.

63
00:06:18,393 --> 00:06:21,863
A long distance call for you
from Dayton, Ohio.

64
00:06:22,073 --> 00:06:25,861
Thank you, l'll be right there.
Must be Father.

65
00:06:26,073 --> 00:06:30,863
l hope nothing's happened.
l'll meet you at my table, dear.

66
00:06:32,793 --> 00:06:38,106
Father! Never misses, Gus' old man.
Right on cue. Too bad, honey.

67
00:06:38,353 --> 00:06:40,787
Nothing's going wrong this time.

68
00:06:40,993 --> 00:06:45,066
The old boy won't let you
commit matrimony with his son.

69
00:06:45,273 --> 00:06:47,912
He'd rather shove him
down an elevator shaft.

70
00:06:48,113 --> 00:06:52,903
Dorothy, l'm sailing on Saturday,
with or without Mr. Esmond.

71
00:06:53,153 --> 00:06:57,112
And l'm not coming back
until he comes and gets me.

72
00:06:57,353 --> 00:07:02,381
When we're in France, where
his father can't call twice a day....

73
00:07:03,273 --> 00:07:05,741
Gus will never let you go alone.

74
00:07:05,953 --> 00:07:11,266
Sometimes Mr. Esmond finds it
very difficult to say no to me.

75
00:07:11,713 --> 00:07:14,352
Well, that's very possible.

76
00:07:24,313 --> 00:07:25,348
(WHISTLE BLOWS)

77
00:07:25,553 --> 00:07:29,387
We can't check the roll
if you don't stick together.

78
00:07:29,593 --> 00:07:34,348
Peters? Randall?
Sanford? Sims?

79
00:07:34,553 --> 00:07:36,430
-Stevens?
-Look at that.

80
00:07:36,593 --> 00:07:39,061
Stevens? Willard J. Stevens?

81
00:07:39,273 --> 00:07:41,662
-Why don't you answer--?
-l'm busy.

82
00:07:41,873 --> 00:07:44,387
(WHISTLING)

83
00:07:44,833 --> 00:07:48,587
-Boy, oh, boy!
-Check your passport over there.

84
00:07:48,793 --> 00:07:52,468
-ls this the way to Europe, France?
-To where?

85
00:07:52,833 --> 00:07:57,270
-No, honey. France is in Europe.
-Who said it wasn't?

86
00:07:57,473 --> 00:08:00,545
Would you say,
""North America, Mexico""?

87
00:08:00,753 --> 00:08:03,745
-lf that's where l wanted to go.
-The dealer passes.

88
00:08:03,953 --> 00:08:08,344
-This ship goes to Cherbourg, France.
-Thank you ever so. See?

89
00:08:08,553 --> 00:08:11,784
What's the talent in the blue jackets?
A band?

90
00:08:11,993 --> 00:08:15,508
That's the Olympic team.
They're sailing on this ship.

91
00:08:15,753 --> 00:08:20,508
The Olympic team, for me?
Wasn't that thoughtful of somebody?

92
00:08:20,713 --> 00:08:23,227
-Dibs on the shot-putter.
-Dorothy Shaw!

93
00:08:23,513 --> 00:08:28,633
-Remember, you're the chaperone.
-Let's get this straight:

94
00:08:28,833 --> 00:08:31,870
The chaperone sees that
nobody else has fun.

95
00:08:32,073 --> 00:08:36,510
Nobody chaperones the chaperone.
That's why l'm right for this job.

96
00:08:36,753 --> 00:08:38,664
TlCKET AGENT :
Passports, please.

97
00:08:39,993 --> 00:08:43,303
l thought you'd be late.
Here's your ticket.

98
00:08:43,513 --> 00:08:47,472
They're at the passport desk.
You're after the blonde.

99
00:08:47,673 --> 00:08:51,302
The brunette's her friend.
We don't care what she does.

100
00:08:51,513 --> 00:08:56,064
-l care.
-Have fun, son.

101
00:08:56,753 --> 00:09:01,702
-Come on, guys, let's get on board.
-Have a nice trip.

102
00:09:12,073 --> 00:09:16,305
Suppose the ship sank. Which one
would you save from drowning?

103
00:09:16,553 --> 00:09:19,067
Those girls couldn't drown.

104
00:09:23,953 --> 00:09:27,070
-Right in here, mademoiselle.
-Thank you.

105
00:09:29,353 --> 00:09:33,392
My, it's just like a room, isn't it?

106
00:09:33,593 --> 00:09:36,869
Oh, look! Round windows!

107
00:09:37,073 --> 00:09:40,827
Yes, dear.
Just put that there, Frisbee.

108
00:09:41,033 --> 00:09:44,821
And, Frisbee, wait for me
on the pier. Lorelei--

109
00:09:45,033 --> 00:09:46,864
-Where's Dorothy?
-l don't know.

110
00:09:47,073 --> 00:09:51,510
Someone whistled and she disappeared.
Will she be a bad influence?

111
00:09:51,753 --> 00:09:56,668
Dorothy's not bad, honest.
She's just dumb.

112
00:09:56,873 --> 00:10:00,707
Always falling for a man
just because he's good-looking.

113
00:10:00,913 --> 00:10:06,863
l keep telling her, it's as easy
to fall for a rich man as a poor man.

114
00:10:07,073 --> 00:10:12,272
lf they're tall, dark and handsome,
she forgets vital statistics.

115
00:10:12,473 --> 00:10:16,705
That's why l'm her friend.
She needs me to educate her.

116
00:10:16,953 --> 00:10:21,663
Yes, but very few girls have
your wonderful willingness to learn.

117
00:10:21,873 --> 00:10:25,912
-l suppose that's true.
-Put this in a safe place.

118
00:10:26,113 --> 00:10:28,263
-What is it?
-A letter of credit.

119
00:10:28,473 --> 00:10:31,863
That's sweet!
You wrote me before l went away.

120
00:10:32,073 --> 00:10:36,112
-No, a letter of credit is like money.
-Money?

121
00:10:36,313 --> 00:10:40,829
-Just take it to a bank in Paris.
-That's wonderful!

122
00:10:41,033 --> 00:10:44,582
Write me every day.
l'll be so lonesome.

123
00:10:44,793 --> 00:10:48,308
l bought you
a little going-away present.

124
00:10:48,513 --> 00:10:50,981
Daddy! Daddy!

125
00:10:51,193 --> 00:10:54,629
There's only one of you
in the whole wide world.

126
00:10:57,193 --> 00:10:59,832
Sorry, wrong room.

127
00:11:01,553 --> 00:11:04,545
-Who's that?
-A stranger. He had the wrong room.

128
00:11:04,753 --> 00:11:07,870
Good-looking.
Hope he isn't just seeing someone off.

129
00:11:08,073 --> 00:11:10,268
Quite a place we have here.

130
00:11:10,513 --> 00:11:13,425
Come in, fellas.
Folks, meet the relay team.

131
00:11:13,633 --> 00:11:15,430
-Hi.
-How do you do?

132
00:11:15,633 --> 00:11:19,672
We're having a bon voyage party.
Put the phonograph in there.

133
00:11:19,873 --> 00:11:25,470
Come on in, everybody. Make yourselves
at home. l'll get the glasses.

134
00:11:27,273 --> 00:11:29,468
MAN:
Who's got the champagne?

135
00:11:30,953 --> 00:11:34,070
Keep those athletes to yourself.

136
00:11:34,273 --> 00:11:37,470
What a coincidence!
That's my plan too.

137
00:11:38,633 --> 00:11:42,228
Gangway! Who needs a glass?

138
00:11:42,513 --> 00:11:46,904
-l want to talk to you.
-Sure.

139
00:11:47,113 --> 00:11:50,230
l want to tell you....

140
00:11:50,433 --> 00:11:54,062
l want to remind you
of something very....

141
00:11:54,313 --> 00:11:58,101
Stop that, please.
lt's most distracting.

142
00:11:58,353 --> 00:12:03,268
Dear, a lot depends on how
you conduct yourself on this trip.

143
00:12:03,473 --> 00:12:07,102
As you know, Dad is dead set
against our marriage.

144
00:12:07,353 --> 00:12:13,064
Even the slightest hint of scandal....
l don't know what l could do.

145
00:12:13,273 --> 00:12:16,663
My goodness, lover.
You don't have to tell me that.

146
00:12:16,873 --> 00:12:20,024
l'd give anything to sail
with you, baby.

147
00:12:20,233 --> 00:12:23,623
Me too. l don't know
what l'll do without you.

148
00:12:24,353 --> 00:12:27,265
l don't know what l'll do without you.

149
00:12:27,513 --> 00:12:31,791
l'm not so sure.
You can be a naughty boy sometimes.

150
00:12:31,993 --> 00:12:37,590
-You don't have to worry about me.
-l do, though.

151
00:12:37,913 --> 00:12:40,905
(MUSIC PLAYS)

152
00:12:42,913 --> 00:12:44,187
(GONG CLANGS)

153
00:12:44,353 --> 00:12:48,665
All visitors ashore! First call.
All visitors ashore!

154
00:12:48,913 --> 00:12:50,790
Bye-bye, baby

155
00:12:51,033 --> 00:12:56,869
Remember you're my baby
When they give you the eye

156
00:12:57,073 --> 00:13:02,591
Although I know that you care
Won't you write and declare

157
00:13:02,793 --> 00:13:09,062
That though on the loose
You are still on the square?

158
00:13:09,273 --> 00:13:13,471
I'll be gloomy
But send that rainbow to me

159
00:13:13,713 --> 00:13:18,070
Then my shadows will fly

160
00:13:18,273 --> 00:13:21,709
Though you'll be gone for a while

161
00:13:21,953 --> 00:13:28,665
I know that I'll be smilin'
With my baby by and by and by

162
00:13:28,873 --> 00:13:34,709
-With my baby by and by
-In the sweet by and by

163
00:13:34,913 --> 00:13:37,029
Bye-bye, baby, bye-bye

164
00:13:37,233 --> 00:13:41,863
-We'll go meet on the beautiful shore
-Baby, bye, goodbye

165
00:13:44,153 --> 00:13:46,109
Bye-bye, pretty baby

166
00:13:46,353 --> 00:13:49,504
You better remember you're my baby

167
00:13:49,753 --> 00:13:53,507
When they give you the eye
My, my!

168
00:13:53,753 --> 00:13:58,873
Although I know that you care
Won't you write and declare

169
00:13:59,073 --> 00:14:05,308
Declare that though on the loose
You are still staying on the square

170
00:14:05,553 --> 00:14:08,067
I'll be gloomy

171
00:14:08,273 --> 00:14:10,662
But send that rainbow to me

172
00:14:10,913 --> 00:14:14,508
Then my shadow will fly

173
00:14:14,753 --> 00:14:18,507
Though you'll be gone for a while

174
00:14:18,753 --> 00:14:25,750
I know that I'll be smilin'
With my baby by and by and by

175
00:14:25,953 --> 00:14:30,868
With my baby by and by

176
00:14:43,833 --> 00:14:49,305
I'll be in my room alone

177
00:14:49,553 --> 00:14:54,104
Every postmeridian

178
00:14:54,353 --> 00:14:58,266
And I'll be with my diary

179
00:14:58,513 --> 00:15:04,861
And that book by Mr. Gideon

180
00:15:06,233 --> 00:15:11,387
Bye-bye, baby

181
00:15:11,633 --> 00:15:17,310
Remember you're my baby

182
00:15:17,553 --> 00:15:24,231
When they give you the eye

183
00:15:25,513 --> 00:15:31,509
And just to show that I care

184
00:15:31,753 --> 00:15:37,510
I will write and declare

185
00:15:37,753 --> 00:15:42,907
That I'm on the loose

186
00:15:43,153 --> 00:15:48,864
But I'll stay on the square

187
00:15:49,913 --> 00:15:55,112
I'll be lonely

188
00:15:55,353 --> 00:16:01,189
But even though I'm lonely

189
00:16:01,393 --> 00:16:07,912
There'll be no other guy

190
00:16:10,073 --> 00:16:17,229
Though I'll be gone for a while

191
00:16:17,433 --> 00:16:23,110
I know that I'll be smilin'

192
00:16:24,033 --> 00:16:28,470
With my baby by and by and by

193
00:16:28,673 --> 00:16:31,870
With my baby by and by

194
00:16:32,113 --> 00:16:37,312
I'll be gloomy
But send that rainbow to me

195
00:16:38,753 --> 00:16:43,508
PORTER: All ashore! Last call!
All ashore! Last call!

196
00:16:45,513 --> 00:16:52,703
I know that I'll be smilin'
With my baby by and by and by

197
00:16:55,593 --> 00:17:01,463
Bye-bye, baby
Remember you're my baby

198
00:17:01,633 --> 00:17:05,421
When they give you the eye

199
00:17:05,593 --> 00:17:11,384
Although I know that you care
Won't you write and declare

200
00:17:11,593 --> 00:17:17,350
That though on the loose
You are still on the square

201
00:17:25,593 --> 00:17:27,868
-You better go.
-Don't go.

202
00:17:28,033 --> 00:17:31,150
-Step back, please.
-Bye, lover!

203
00:17:31,313 --> 00:17:38,230
I know that I'll be smilin'
With my baby by and by

204
00:17:38,393 --> 00:17:40,349
And by

205
00:17:40,513 --> 00:17:44,984
With my wonderful baby

206
00:17:45,633 --> 00:17:53,472
By and by

207
00:18:07,233 --> 00:18:09,463
-Hi.
-Hi.

208
00:18:11,633 --> 00:18:15,672
-Hi, Miss Shaw.
-All right, guys, keep moving.

209
00:18:17,793 --> 00:18:22,992
-""Mr. Amos Jones and valet.""
-What are you doing?

210
00:18:23,753 --> 00:18:28,747
Checking the passenger list.
""Mr. Alfred Loman and valet.""

211
00:18:28,953 --> 00:18:31,865
""Mr. Eugene Martin and valet.""

212
00:18:32,113 --> 00:18:34,832
Why the sudden interest in valets?

213
00:18:35,033 --> 00:18:39,663
When a man has ""and valet""
after his name, he's worthwhile.

214
00:18:39,873 --> 00:18:42,706
l'm trying to find
a gentleman escort for you.

215
00:18:42,953 --> 00:18:47,390
Don't bother. l just
provided myself with about 20.

216
00:18:48,233 --> 00:18:51,782
Dorothy, did you ever hear
of a rich pole-vaulter?

217
00:18:51,993 --> 00:18:56,783
Who cares? l like a man
who can run faster than l can.

218
00:18:56,993 --> 00:18:59,109
l hate to think where you'll wind up.

219
00:18:59,313 --> 00:19:02,828
You're wasting time on
unrefined persons without money.

220
00:19:03,033 --> 00:19:06,742
Did it occur to you that
some people don't care about money?

221
00:19:06,993 --> 00:19:09,746
Don't be silly.
We're talking serious.

222
00:19:10,353 --> 00:19:14,266
-Do you want a loveless marriage?
-Me, loveless?

223
00:19:14,553 --> 00:19:19,104
lf a girl spends time worrying
about the money she doesn't have...

224
00:19:19,313 --> 00:19:21,986
...how will she have
any time for love?

225
00:19:22,193 --> 00:19:26,505
l want you to find happiness
and stop having fun.

226
00:19:26,753 --> 00:19:30,985
-That baffles me.
-You'll thank me some day.

227
00:19:31,193 --> 00:19:36,313
Here's a good one:
""Henry Spofford lll and valet.""

228
00:19:36,513 --> 00:19:40,984
l remember. The Spofford family
owns practically a whole state.

229
00:19:41,193 --> 00:19:44,390
A big one too.
l think it's Pennsylvania.

230
00:19:44,593 --> 00:19:47,505
l guess l could settle
for Pennsylvania.

231
00:19:47,713 --> 00:19:52,628
-Hello, Mrs. Henry Spofford lll.
-Mrs. Henry Spofford lll and valet.

232
00:19:52,833 --> 00:19:55,905
He won't have anything l don't.
See you later.

233
00:19:56,113 --> 00:19:59,662
Don't forget the cocktail party. 5:30.

234
00:20:05,393 --> 00:20:08,271
-The whole team?
-Until after the games.

235
00:20:08,473 --> 00:20:12,227
-You eat at 6 and go to bed at 9?
-That's right.

236
00:20:12,433 --> 00:20:14,025
Coach is strict.

