No, no

815
01:07:46,113 --> 01:07:50,072
No, no, no, no, no, no, no

816
01:07:50,233 --> 01:07:51,951
No!

817
01:07:54,673 --> 01:07:59,303
The French are glad to die for love

818
01:07:59,553 --> 01:08:04,468
They delight in fighting duels

819
01:08:04,673 --> 01:08:08,063
But I prefer a man who lives

820
01:08:08,273 --> 01:08:14,906
And gives expensive jewels

821
01:08:15,113 --> 01:08:19,903
A kiss on the hand
May be quite continental

822
01:08:20,153 --> 01:08:24,908
But diamonds are a girl's best friend

823
01:08:25,153 --> 01:08:28,065
A kiss may be grand

824
01:08:28,313 --> 01:08:32,101
But it won't pay the rental
On your humble flat

825
01:08:32,353 --> 01:08:35,186
Or help you at the automat

826
01:08:35,433 --> 01:08:39,904
Men grow cold as girls grow old

827
01:08:40,153 --> 01:08:44,908
And we all lose our charms in the end

828
01:08:45,153 --> 01:08:49,863
But square-cut or pear-shaped
These rocks don't lose their shape

829
01:08:50,353 --> 01:08:55,302
Diamonds are a girl's best friend

830
01:08:56,553 --> 01:08:58,908
Tiffany's!

831
01:09:01,473 --> 01:09:03,782
Cartier!

832
01:09:05,153 --> 01:09:07,383
Black, Starr, Frost, Gorham

833
01:09:07,633 --> 01:09:11,262
Talk to me, Harry Winston
Tell me all about it!

834
01:09:14,953 --> 01:09:19,663
There may come a time
When a lass needs a lawyer

835
01:09:19,873 --> 01:09:24,583
But diamonds are a girl's best friend

836
01:09:24,833 --> 01:09:26,710
There may come a time

837
01:09:26,953 --> 01:09:32,107
When a hard-boiled employer
Thinks you're awful nice

838
01:09:32,353 --> 01:09:35,311
But get that ice
Or else no dice

839
01:09:35,553 --> 01:09:39,592
He's your guy when stocks are high

840
01:09:39,833 --> 01:09:44,702
But beware when they start to descend

841
01:09:44,953 --> 01:09:50,073
It's then that those louses
Go back to their spouses

842
01:09:50,273 --> 01:09:54,152
Diamonds are a girl's best friend

843
01:10:02,353 --> 01:10:07,188
I've heard of affairs
That are strictly platonic

844
01:10:07,433 --> 01:10:11,904
But diamonds are a girl's best friend

845
01:10:12,153 --> 01:10:16,908
And I think affairs that
You must keep liaisonic

846
01:10:17,153 --> 01:10:22,466
Are better bets
If little pets get big baguettes

847
01:10:22,673 --> 01:10:26,666
Time rolls on
And youth is gone

848
01:10:26,913 --> 01:10:31,191
And you can't straighten up
When you bend

849
01:10:32,033 --> 01:10:37,107
But stiff back or stiff knees
You stand straight at...

850
01:10:37,353 --> 01:10:41,744
... Tiffany's

851
01:10:46,113 --> 01:10:48,627
Diamonds

852
01:10:51,233 --> 01:10:53,872
Diamonds

853
01:10:56,713 --> 01:11:00,865
I don't mean rhinestones

854
01:11:01,073 --> 01:11:04,065
But diamonds

855
01:11:04,673 --> 01:11:07,870
Are a girl's best

856
01:11:10,513 --> 01:11:13,107
Best friend

857
01:11:22,313 --> 01:11:27,148
-How did Gus like your number?
-He looked kind of grim.

858
01:11:27,353 --> 01:11:29,309
Hand me my hat, please.

859
01:11:29,513 --> 01:11:33,028
He is sweet, isn't he?
l really do love Gus.

860
01:11:33,233 --> 01:11:34,507
You do?

861
01:11:34,713 --> 01:11:38,388
There's no other millionaire
with such a gentle disposition.

862
01:11:38,593 --> 01:11:41,983
He never wins an argument,
does anything l ask...

863
01:11:42,193 --> 01:11:46,823
...and he's got the money to do it.
How can l help loving him?

864
01:11:47,033 --> 01:11:49,706
l guess so.
Let's don't talk about love.

865
01:11:49,953 --> 01:11:52,786
lt reminds me of Malone,
the human ferret.

866
01:11:52,953 --> 01:11:54,591
(KNOCKlNG)

867
01:11:54,753 --> 01:11:57,347
(SPEAKS lN FRENCH)

868
01:11:57,513 --> 01:12:02,507
The police are here!
They have a warrant for your arrest.

869
01:12:02,753 --> 01:12:06,871
lt will get in the newspapers.
lt will hurt my business.

870
01:12:08,513 --> 01:12:10,265
Give up that tiara.

871
01:12:10,513 --> 01:12:13,710
lf l give it back,
it's admitting l stole it.

872
01:12:13,913 --> 01:12:18,111
You're in a strange country.
You can't prove you didn't steal it.

873
01:12:18,313 --> 01:12:21,305
Do you want to go to the Bastille?

874
01:12:21,513 --> 01:12:24,027
-l guess l'll give it back.
-Where is it?

875
01:12:24,233 --> 01:12:26,383
-ln there.
-Come on, let's get it.

876
01:12:26,553 --> 01:12:30,671
-Oh, Dorothy. lt's just not fair.
-No, of course not.

877
01:12:33,073 --> 01:12:34,301
lt's gone!

878
01:12:34,513 --> 01:12:37,664
What? Are you sure
this is where you left it?

879
01:12:37,913 --> 01:12:41,110
Yes. lt's been stolen!
lt's been stolen!

880
01:12:41,273 --> 01:12:42,308
(KNOCKlNG)

881
01:12:42,473 --> 01:12:47,103
The cops!
Sister, we really are in a jam.

882
01:12:47,313 --> 01:12:49,269
Come on.

883
01:12:49,633 --> 01:12:53,467
-l'll give you a boost.
GUS: Lorelei? lt's me, Gus.

884
01:12:53,673 --> 01:12:57,632
-He's your best chance.
-He can't boost me any higher than you.

885
01:12:57,793 --> 01:12:58,669
GUS: Lorelei?

886
01:12:58,833 --> 01:13:03,748
Just a minute. Either you hock
your stuff or get the money from him.

887
01:13:03,953 --> 01:13:07,741
-How much will a tiara cost?
-15,000 at least.

888
01:13:07,953 --> 01:13:12,583
-That'll take an hour and 45 minutes.
-l'll take care of the gendarmes.

889
01:13:12,753 --> 01:13:14,027
How?

890
01:13:14,193 --> 01:13:16,991
You're not the only one here
with hidden talents.

891
01:13:17,153 --> 01:13:19,189
GUS: Lorelei?
-Coming!

892
01:13:20,193 --> 01:13:21,990
You can come in now.

893
01:13:22,193 --> 01:13:26,869
l've made up my mind.
We're through. Through forever.

894
01:13:27,073 --> 01:13:31,066
-First l want to kiss you goodbye.
-Very well.

895
01:13:31,273 --> 01:13:37,667
No, no. Not in front of everybody.
Come on in, Daddy darling.

896
01:13:39,433 --> 01:13:43,472
