934
01:16:42,473 --> 01:16:44,703
Won't you tell me what to say?

935
01:16:44,913 --> 01:16:49,941
-Please to answer the charge.
-Yes, l was going to.

936
01:16:50,433 --> 01:16:55,302
l was just thinking. lt was
all a terrible misunderstanding.

937
01:16:55,513 --> 01:16:59,506
You see, sometimes life is
very hard for a girl like l.

938
01:16:59,753 --> 01:17:04,065
Especially if she's pretty
like l and has blonde hair.

939
01:17:04,313 --> 01:17:07,942
We can do without the philosophy.
Facts only.

940
01:17:08,153 --> 01:17:13,386
Mr. Pritchard is a little confused
and would like to ask a question.

941
01:17:13,593 --> 01:17:16,187
l can hardly blame him.
What is it?

942
01:17:16,433 --> 01:17:21,507
He doesn't see well, and would like
to look at Miss Lee more closely.

943
01:17:21,753 --> 01:17:23,664
Permission granted.

944
01:17:28,153 --> 01:17:31,031
Mr. Pritchard, how nice to see you!

945
01:17:31,233 --> 01:17:34,430
Yes, Miss Lee--
You are Miss Lee, aren't you?

946
01:17:34,633 --> 01:17:39,070
That's who l am, all right.
But my friends call me Lorelei.

947
01:17:39,273 --> 01:17:44,552
l hope you're my friend. l love to
have handsome gentlemen be my friends.

948
01:17:44,833 --> 01:17:46,903
My eyes are not that good.

949
01:17:47,113 --> 01:17:49,308
-Have you ever heard me sing?
-No.

950
01:17:49,513 --> 01:17:52,630
-Are you sure?
-l've not had the pleasure.

951
01:17:52,833 --> 01:17:54,551
Thank you ever so!

952
01:17:54,953 --> 01:17:59,868
A kiss on the hand
May be quite continental

953
01:18:00,113 --> 01:18:04,982
But diamonds are a girl's best friend

954
01:18:05,193 --> 01:18:07,388
A kiss may be grand

955
01:18:08,233 --> 01:18:12,226
But it won't pay the rental
On your humble flat

956
01:18:12,433 --> 01:18:15,266
Or help you at the automat

957
01:18:15,513 --> 01:18:19,984
Men grow cold as girls grow old

958
01:18:20,233 --> 01:18:24,784
And we all lose our charms in the end

959
01:18:25,713 --> 01:18:30,468
Square-cut or pear-shaped
These rocks don't lose their shape

960
01:18:30,713 --> 01:18:32,590
Diamonds are a girl's best friend

961
01:18:32,753 --> 01:18:36,268
This is not a cabaret!
Stop that woman!

962
01:18:36,873 --> 01:18:38,465
Tiffany's!

963
01:18:41,513 --> 01:18:43,663
Cartier!

964
01:18:49,953 --> 01:18:52,308
Black, Starr, Frost, Gorham

965
01:18:52,553 --> 01:18:55,431
Talk to me, Harry Winston
Talk to me

966
01:18:55,633 --> 01:18:59,945
Did you hear me? Stop her!
Get her to the witness stand!

967
01:19:00,153 --> 01:19:03,543
The rest of you take your places.

968
01:19:04,473 --> 01:19:06,304
You are fired!

969
01:19:06,513 --> 01:19:09,232
How could my son get mixed up
with that type of girl?

970
01:19:09,393 --> 01:19:11,065
(SPEAKS lN FRENCH)

971
01:19:14,633 --> 01:19:18,945
Now, young lady,
we're here to dispense justice.

972
01:19:19,153 --> 01:19:22,862
Not to watch a cabaret show.
You understand me?

973
01:19:23,073 --> 01:19:26,463
-Yes, judge.
-All right.

974
01:19:26,673 --> 01:19:30,063
Did you or did you not steal
the diamond tiara?

975
01:19:30,313 --> 01:19:33,225
Oh, no, sir. l did not steal it.

976
01:19:33,433 --> 01:19:37,392
The fact is, Lady Beekman's
husband gave it to me.

977
01:19:37,593 --> 01:19:39,902
Your Honor! The defendant is not--

978
01:19:40,073 --> 01:19:41,904
(SPEAKS lN FRENCH)

979
01:19:43,473 --> 01:19:47,944
-You have evidence for this case?
-Yes, l have.

980
01:19:48,153 --> 01:19:50,872
Before he talks,
could l explain something?

981
01:19:51,073 --> 01:19:52,631
JUDGE: Go ahead.

982
01:19:52,833 --> 01:19:58,271
l have a friend named Dorothy,
and she's a really good friend.

983
01:19:58,473 --> 01:20:02,148
She knows l would never do
anything really wrong.

984
01:20:02,353 --> 01:20:07,427
-Do you have to say this?
-Yes, sir, l do.

985
01:20:07,633 --> 01:20:12,912
There's a young man that Dorothy likes.
She's very fond of him.

986
01:20:13,113 --> 01:20:16,583
Dorothy would never speak
to this man again...

987
01:20:16,793 --> 01:20:20,866
...if he did anything
to hurt me, Lorelei.

988
01:20:21,073 --> 01:20:25,271
So l think this young man had
just better know that...

989
01:20:26,233 --> 01:20:29,703
...Dorothy thinks
she's in love with him.

990
01:20:30,433 --> 01:20:33,869
Mr. Esmond, l resign.
l just quit the case.

991
01:20:34,073 --> 01:20:35,586
Are you crazy?

992
01:20:35,793 --> 01:20:39,672
But l like it that way.
Judge, l've changed my mind.

993
01:20:39,873 --> 01:20:42,512
l haven't anything to say.

994
01:20:42,713 --> 01:20:45,625
JUDGE:
This becomes more and more confusing.

995
01:20:45,833 --> 01:20:50,861
But the solution is simple.
My decision is this:

996
01:20:51,073 --> 01:20:54,349
The property will be placed
in this court's custody...

997
01:20:54,553 --> 01:21:00,025
...until the owner can be established
by an affidavit from Lord Beekman.

998
01:21:00,233 --> 01:21:04,272
Now, Miss Lee, you will
give me the tiara.

999
01:21:04,513 --> 01:21:08,506
-But l can't.
JUDGE: lf you refuse, you go to prison.

1000
01:21:08,713 --> 01:21:11,910
l just haven't got it.
lt was stolen.

1001
01:21:12,153 --> 01:21:15,668
l think l know where that thing is,
and who's got it.

1002
01:21:15,873 --> 01:21:18,990
JUDGE: Who are you?
-A private detective.

1003
01:21:19,193 --> 01:21:24,142
Give me two policemen and wait
half an hour. l can settle this.

1004
01:21:24,353 --> 01:21:26,821
Anything would be better than this.
Go with him.

1005
01:21:26,993 --> 01:21:32,590
(SPEAKlNG lN FRENCH)

1006
01:21:34,393 --> 01:21:36,065
There he is.

1007
01:21:37,913 --> 01:21:39,904
(SPEAKlNG lN FRENCH)

1008
01:21:40,073 --> 01:21:41,870
What's that?

1009
01:21:42,273 --> 01:21:44,264
What's he saying?

1010
01:21:44,913 --> 01:21:48,428
Speak English!
This is outrageous!

1011
01:21:48,633 --> 01:21:50,828
l'm a British subject!

1012
01:21:51,033 --> 01:21:54,582
This is positively outrageous!
l demand a lawyer.

1013
01:21:54,753 --> 01:21:56,584
(SPEAKlNG lN FRENCH)

1014
01:21:56,753 --> 01:21:57,742
What?

1015
01:21:57,913 --> 01:22:01,701
-What did you say?
-He says remove your hat.

1016
01:22:01,953 --> 01:22:05,070
Why doesn't he say so?
Send for the consulate.

1017
01:22:05,313 --> 01:22:07,668
-l'll take this.
-Give that back.

1018
01:22:07,873 --> 01:22:12,901
This is Sir Francis Beekman.
And this is the missing tiara.

1019
01:22:13,113 --> 01:22:16,150
-That's mine!
-Miss Lee will be glad to return it.

1020
01:22:16,353 --> 01:22:18,230
l certainly would.

1021
01:22:18,433 --> 01:22:22,472
l believe His Honor asked
Miss Lee for the tiara.

1022
01:22:22,713 --> 01:22:26,467
-l say, that isn't--
-l wouldn't go into that, Mr. Finch.

1023
01:22:26,633 --> 01:22:27,827
Finch?

1024
01:22:27,993 --> 01:22:30,666
-Miss Lee.
-Thank you.

1025
01:22:33,193 --> 01:22:36,071
-Your Honor.
-Thank you.

1026
01:22:36,713 --> 01:22:38,669
Thank you.

1027
01:22:40,153 --> 01:22:43,225
-Monsieur Pritchard.
-Thank you. Your Lordship.

1028
01:22:43,433 --> 01:22:44,422
Thank you.

1029
01:22:45,273 --> 01:22:47,229
Case dismissed!

1030
01:22:48,153 --> 01:22:50,542
Five minutes ago
you said you'd marry me.

1031
01:22:50,753 --> 01:22:55,304
-That's before Dorothy phoned.
-What made you change your mind?

1032
01:22:55,513 --> 01:22:58,311
She just said everything's okay now.

1033
01:22:58,513 --> 01:23:02,950
l don't quite understand--
Oh, dear. Hello, Father.

1034
01:23:03,193 --> 01:23:04,626
Hello, son.

1035
01:23:04,833 --> 01:23:09,270
l know why you're here, and l don't
care. l'll make her marry me.

1036
01:23:09,473 --> 01:23:11,384
That's wonderful.

1037
01:23:11,593 --> 01:23:16,030
l presume this is the young lady?
A pretty girl. American?

1038
01:23:16,233 --> 01:23:18,986
Yes, except on my parents' side.
They're lrish.

1039
01:23:19,193 --> 01:23:24,267
l'm delighted. l've wanted to
see you married for a long time.

1040
01:23:24,473 --> 01:23:27,271
Anybody but that monster,
Lorelei Lee.

1041
01:23:27,473 --> 01:23:31,102
But, Mr. Esmond, l am Lorelei Lee!

1042
01:23:31,353 --> 01:23:34,504
Pretty early to start teasing
your father-in-law.

1043
01:23:34,713 --> 01:23:38,547
-What's the matter, Father?
-Nothing. l can take a joke.

1044
01:23:38,753 --> 01:23:43,463
What joke? This is Lorelei.
This is nothing to joke about.

1045
01:23:43,713 --> 01:23:48,548
l don't have my driver's license
with me, but take my word for it.

1046
01:23:48,793 --> 01:23:53,071
Look, that's l.
See my name?

1047
01:23:53,673 --> 01:23:55,186
FATHER: Oh....

1048
01:23:55,553 --> 01:23:57,987
l'm too old for this sort of thing.

1049
01:23:58,193 --> 01:24:00,946
-l don't understand.
-You don't understand?

1050
01:24:01,153 --> 01:24:05,226
How do you think l feel with
thousands of Lorelei Lees around me?

1051
01:24:05,433 --> 01:24:08,231
But you're not marrying any of them!

1052
01:24:08,433 --> 01:24:12,142
l love her. l love her very much.
l've never felt--

1053
01:24:12,353 --> 01:24:17,188
Oh, shut up! Young lady,
you don't fool me one bit.

1054
01:24:17,393 --> 01:24:20,590
l'm not trying to.
But l bet l could.

1055
01:24:20,833 --> 01:24:25,190
You might convince this jackass,
but you'll never convince me.

1056
01:24:25,393 --> 01:24:30,228
-That's too bad. l do love him.
-Certainly. For his money.

1057
01:24:30,433 --> 01:24:32,424
No! Honestly.

1058
01:24:32,713 --> 01:24:37,468
You expect me to believe that you
aren't marrying him for his money?

1059
01:24:37,753 --> 01:24:41,029
-lt's true.
-Then why do you want to marry him?

1060
01:24:41,233 --> 01:24:45,306
-l want to marry him for your money.
-There!

1061
01:24:46,633 --> 01:24:49,306
That's why we need his consent, silly.

1062
01:24:49,513 --> 01:24:53,870
We're getting down to brass tacks.
You admit you're after money.

1063
01:24:54,113 --> 01:24:57,503
No, l don't.
Aren't you funny?

1064
01:24:57,713 --> 01:25:01,945
Don't you know that a rich man
is like a pretty girl?

1065
01:25:02,193 --> 01:25:04,946
You don't marry her
just because she's pretty.

1066
01:25:05,153 --> 01:25:07,542
But, my goodness, doesn't it help?

1067
01:25:07,753 --> 01:25:11,792
Would you want your daughter
to marry a poor man?

1068
01:25:11,993 --> 01:25:16,464
You'd want her to have the most
wonderful things in the world.

1069
01:25:16,673 --> 01:25:19,312
Why is it wrong for me
to want those things?

1070
01:25:19,553 --> 01:25:21,464
Well, l concede that--

1071
01:25:21,673 --> 01:25:25,552
Say, they told me you were stupid.
You don't sound stupid.

1072
01:25:25,793 --> 01:25:29,945
l can be smart when it's important.
But most men don't like it.

1073
01:25:30,153 --> 01:25:33,782
Except Gus.
He's interested in my brains.

1074
01:25:34,033 --> 01:25:38,743
-No, that much of a fool he's not.
-You've changed your mind?

1075
01:25:38,993 --> 01:25:44,545
-l just don't know what to tell you.
-Daddy?

1076
01:25:44,793 --> 01:25:47,546
Not you. l guess l mean ""Sonny.""

1077
01:25:47,793 --> 01:25:51,069
Give me three minutes
alone with your father.

1078
01:25:51,273 --> 01:25:54,026
-Run along, darling.
-Yes, dear.

1079
01:25:54,233 --> 01:25:56,747
Now, about what we were speaking.

1080
01:25:56,953 --> 01:26:01,105
There's a great deal to consider.
l just can't answer....

1081
01:26:11,873 --> 01:26:14,910
Please, take your places.

1082
01:26:27,993 --> 01:26:32,305
Remember, on your wedding day
it's all right to say yes.

1083
01:26:36,393 --> 01:26:42,707
We're just two little girls
From Little Rock

1084
01:26:43,993 --> 01:26:50,182
And we lived on the wrong side
Of the tracks

1085
01:26:51,433 --> 01:26:55,346
But at last we won the big crusade

1086
01:26:55,593 --> 01:27:01,031
Looks like we finally made the grade

1087
01:27:05,353 --> 01:27:15,342
Square-cut or pear-shaped
These rocks don't lose their shape

1088
01:27:15,633 --> 01:27:21,105
Diamonds
Diamonds

1089
01:27:21,273 --> 01:27:27,303
Diamonds are a girl's...
Diamonds are a girl's...

1090
01:27:27,473 --> 01:27:31,910
...best friend
